			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Shuriken of Eternity, worth it?<a name="49474"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 1 04 7:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I know there's probably a monk or two who might see this thread and then go out and try and find a hit man to take me out, but here it is none the less.
<br />

<br />
We spend 6 AA's on for what is probably the second-most useful AA we get besides Fading Memories --- Bellow.  It's an instant-tagging device with long range, and extremely handy for pulling.
<br />

<br />
That being said, it has an extreme deficiency that no amount of AA's can over-come, - A recast time of 18 seconds.  That makes it's use for mass-pulling(Which you do ALOT of on raids) pretty limited.
<br />

<br />
However, there is a possable Alternative Available --- From Rallos Zek, in the Plane of Time, the Pouch of Eternity, which summons 20 Shurikens of Eternity --- 250 Range each, 15 delay, very nice stats.  With Haste, a Bard could probably throw one of these every .75 to 1 second(just keep up over-haste on pulls), which is a good deal faster than using songs to tag mobs, and with even less agro during the pull.
<br />

<br />
I've been debating on getting one for quite awhile now...however, I've already bought a good Time-ranged item(Globe of Mystical protection), so I've been wary about getting a second one, as my guild uses a DKP-based system and you have to be frugal about your spending, not to mention I may well risk angering more than a few monks in guild for taking it, after barely managing to become &quot;tolerated&quot; and almost even liked by them since I joined and took over pulling in the guild.
<br />

<br />

<br />
So does anyone actually have this item and uses it often on pulls to give some input here?</span></td>
