				<td colspan="2"><span>This reminds me that I've been meaning to ask if anyone knows how the DPS compares between: 
<br />
Chants while meleeing with Edge of Eternity + Songblade
<br />
Chants on a Rathe drum while throwing Shirukens of Eternity
<br />

<br />
My gut feeling is that the shirukens will miss too much to be as useful in melee situations.  Can still use while kiting, or while playing Veeshan/Marr on clerics though.
<br />

<br />
On other assorted topics...  Castersrealm lists Bard throwing cap at 113.  Not sure if this is still accurate as my throwing is not yet capped.  A result of low intellegence in my youth, I suppose.
<br />

<br />
Rogues get throwing crits and the highest throwing cap, so would do more damage than monks with the shirukens.  However, rogues can also use bows (albeit without crits) while monks can't.  So it seems easier for rogues to get a ranged weapon with decent stats than monks, I suppose.  
<br />

<br />
For those looking for a mere 250 range throwing item for occasional pulling, Antonian Javolins were made stackable at some point, I believe.  I haven't bothered to make any since I bought boastful bellow, and they are only useable by human/half-elf/erudite/barbarian, if I recall correctly.
