				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Shuriken of Eternity, worth it?<a name="49593"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 1 04 5:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't know much about the shuriken issue but my gut tells me chants with Rathe drum + shurikens will do less damage than pure dots + melee.
<br />

<br />
My reasoning is as follow:
<br />

<br />
1) As you stated, throwing is capped at 113(which is what EQdiva has listed so I assume is correct, barring interference from the multitude of skill up bugs lately). When using a ranged item, you wont be able to gain the benefit of dual wielding your non-instrument hand in melee, as you would while meleeing with a drum.
<br />

<br />
2) When comparing rathe drum mod to melee, you probably have some other sort of percussion mod through equipment. This definitely closes the gap between the rathe(capped most likely) mod and no rathe mod. The question now is does the weapon in your main hand put out enough damage to cover the mod difference between the rathe drum and whatever other mods you are wearing.
<br />

<br />
I think in most cases, the melee in main hand will outdo the mod difference, thus offering you better DPS meleeing with two weapons and singing dots.
<br />

<br />
Of course then theres the issue of resists which hurts chant DPS in general, throwing the comparison once again more in favor of have both arms melee.</span></td>
